        "rendered": "Heading block"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go back to the list of <strong>Blocks</strong></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Headings help to introduce new sections and organize the content on the page. They make your website more readable by humans and search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add a heading, click on the <strong>Block Inserter</strong> (<strong>+</strong>). Alternatively, you can type&nbsp;<code>/heading</code> in a new paragraph block and press <code>enter</code>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add a Heading block with <strong>H1</strong> heading level by typing <code>/h1</code> in a new paragraph block followed by <code>enter</code>. Subsequent heading blocks can be added by typing <code>/h2</code>, <code>/h3</code>, <code>/h4</code>, <code>/h5</code>, <code>/h6</code> followed by <code>enter</code>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Block editor by default considers the page title as the &lt;h1&gt; tag, so subsequent&nbsp;<strong>Heading</strong> blocks&nbsp;are added as <strong>H2</strong>, <strong>H3</strong>, and so on. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also choose your heading level according to your style from the Block Toolbar.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"900\" height=\"636\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.18.34-AM.png\" alt=\"Changing the heading levels in the Heading block\" class=\"wp-image-15761396\" style=\"width:450px;height:318px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.18.34-AM.png 900w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.18.34-AM-300x212.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.18.34-AM-768x543.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another shortcut method to add a heading is to type <code>##space</code> to add <strong>H2</strong> heading, <code>###space</code> to add <strong>H3</strong> heading, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/02/heading_block_markdown.mp4\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks </a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"block-toolbar\">Block toolbar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Each block has its own block-specific controls that allow you to customize the block right in the editor. The&nbsp;<strong>Heading</strong> block&nbsp;offers the following options in its toolbar:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Transform to</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Drag icon</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Move handles</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Change alignment</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Change heading level</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Change text alignment</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bold</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Italic</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Link</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More rich text controls</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More options</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"890\" height=\"386\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.51.28-AM.png\" alt=\"The heading block toolbar \" class=\"wp-image-15761515\" style=\"width:445px;height:193px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.51.28-AM.png 890w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.51.28-AM-300x130.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.51.28-AM-768x333.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 890px) 100vw, 890px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The heading block toolbar </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Transform to</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When you click on the&nbsp;<strong>Transform</strong>&nbsp;button you can convert the Heading block<em>&nbsp;</em>into a Paragraph, List, Quote, Columns, Pullquote, or Group block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"930\" height=\"728\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.31.54-AM.png\" alt=\"Transform option in the Heading block\" class=\"wp-image-16269678\" style=\"width:465px;height:364px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.31.54-AM.png 930w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.31.54-AM-300x235.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.31.54-AM-768x601.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 930px) 100vw, 930px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Drag icon</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.55.20-AM-1.png\" alt=\"Drag option in the Heading block\" class=\"wp-image-15761524\" style=\"width:443px;height:70px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To drag and drop the block to a new location on the page template, click and hold the rectangle of dots, then drag to the new location. The blue separator line indicates where the block will be placed. Release the left mouse button when you find the new location to place the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Move handles</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"914\" height=\"142\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.56.30-AM.png\" alt=\"Move handles in the Heading block\" class=\"wp-image-15761527\" style=\"width:457px;height:71px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.56.30-AM.png 914w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.56.30-AM-300x47.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.56.30-AM-768x119.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 914px) 100vw, 914px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The up and down arrow icons can be used to move a block up and down on the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/moving-blocks/\" target=\"_blank\">Get more information about moving a block within the editor.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Change alignment </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the alignment drop-down from the toolbar, you can make the&nbsp;Heading block&nbsp;wide width or full width. The wide-width and the full-width align options are only available if your theme supports them.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"896\" height=\"418\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.58.58-AM.png\" alt=\"Change alignment in the Heading block\" class=\"wp-image-15761533\" style=\"width:448px;height:209px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.58.58-AM.png 896w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.58.58-AM-300x140.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-9.58.58-AM-768x358.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 896px) 100vw, 896px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Change heading level</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can change the heading levels from <strong>H1</strong> through <strong>H6</strong> from the block toolbar.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"890\" height=\"638\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-10.00.04-AM.png\" alt=\"Change heading level in the Heading block\" class=\"wp-image-15761537\" style=\"width:445px;height:319px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-10.00.04-AM.png 890w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-10.00.04-AM-300x215.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-10.00.04-AM-768x551.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 890px) 100vw, 890px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Change text alignment</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"932\" height=\"402\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.40.59-AM.png\" alt=\"Change the text alignment in the Heading block\" class=\"wp-image-16269708\" style=\"width:466px;height:201px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.40.59-AM.png 932w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.40.59-AM-300x129.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.40.59-AM-768x331.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 932px) 100vw, 932px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Block toolbar with the drop-down for alignment.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the alignment drop-down from the toolbar, you are able to align the whole heading text to the left, make it center-aligned or orient it to the right.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Bold</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the <strong>Bold</strong> option or <kbd>Ctrl+B </kbd>/ <kbd>Cmd+B</kbd> on your keyboard to bold it, which is usually heavier than the surrounding text.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Italic</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the <strong>Italic</strong> option or <kbd>Ctrl+I</kbd> / <kbd>Cmd+I</kbd> on your keyboard to italicize it, which usually appears slanted to the right.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Link</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the link icon to insert a hyperlink to the highlighted heading text.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/link-editing/\">Read about more link editing options.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">More rich text options</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The drop-down menu to the left of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">More options menu</a>&nbsp;contains a range of additional rich text editing options such as highlighting, inline code, strikethrough, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-text-editing-overview/\">Read about more rich text editing options.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">More options </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>These controls give you the option to copy, duplicate, and edit your block as HTML.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">Read about these and other settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"block-settings\">Block Settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Every block has specific options in the editor sidebar in addition to the options found in the block toolbar.&nbsp;If you do not see the sidebar, click the <strong>cog</strong> icon next to the <strong>Publish</strong> or <strong>Update</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.02.07-AM.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"668\" height=\"196\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.02.07-AM.png\" alt=\"Block settings in the sidebar\" class=\"wp-image-15761684\" style=\"width:334px;height:98px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.02.07-AM.png 668w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.02.07-AM-300x88.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 668px) 100vw, 668px\" /></a><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The block settings can be found in the sidebar.<br></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Color </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can customize the text color, and background color, for the Heading block.&nbsp;The color options available will vary based on the theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"592\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.06.19-AM-1024x592.png\" alt=\"Color settings in the Heading block\" class=\"wp-image-15761699\" style=\"width:256px;height:148px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.06.19-AM-1024x592.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.06.19-AM-300x173.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.06.19-AM-768x444.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.06.19-AM.png 1156w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Color settings in the Heading block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\">See this guide for more information about changing colors.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Typography </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Typography settings allow you to adjust the Font size, Appearance, Letter case, Line height, and Letter spacing.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"538\" height=\"634\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.25.05-AM.png\" alt=\"Typography settings in the Heading block\" class=\"wp-image-15761755\" style=\"width:269px;height:317px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.25.05-AM.png 538w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-22-at-11.25.05-AM-255x300.png 255w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 538px) 100vw, 538px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Typography settings in the Heading block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/typography-settings-overview/\">Get more details about changing typography settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Dimensions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Dimension controls are used to control how groups of blocks are placed alongside one another, by changing the values for padding, margin, and other dimensions</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/dimension-controls-overview/\">Learn more about dimension controls.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-heading-3-font-size\">Advanced</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the advanced panel of the block options, you\u2019ll see options for HTML Anchor and Additional CSS Class.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.43.58-AM.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"556\" height=\"692\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.43.58-AM.png\" alt=\"You can add HTML Anchors and CSS classes from the sidebar.\" class=\"wp-image-16269724\" style=\"width:278px;height:346px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.43.58-AM.png 556w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/12/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-10.43.58-AM-241x300.png 241w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 556px) 100vw, 556px\" /></a><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">You can add HTML Anchors and CSS classes from the sidebar.<br></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cHTML anchor\u201d allows you to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/page-jumps/\">make a unique web address</a>&nbsp;for a particular Heading block. Then, you\u2019ll be able to link directly to the Heading block of your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The \u201cAdditional CSS class(es)\u201d lets you add CSS class(es) to your block, allowing you to write custom CSS and style the block as you see fit.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-very-dark-gray-color has-very-light-gray-background-color has-text-color has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\" id=\"changelog\">Changelog </h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated 2023-03-07\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added missing ALT tag for text alignment image</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-08-09\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Replaced the link section with short summary linking to new dedicated page.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-06-08\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Replaced &#8220;More rich text options&#8221; section with short summary linking to new dedicated page for rich text editing options.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-06-22\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated content and screenshots for 6.0</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added ALT tags for the images</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-02-04\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added further update for WP 5.9</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2021-02-28\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added images and updated for WP 5.7</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2020-08-27\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added images for WP 5.5</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2020-06-18\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added &#8216;Link back to blocks&#8217; to the top of the page</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added the &#8216;Changelog&#8217;</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2019-03-07</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
